Package com.intellij.codeInspection.dataFlow

Class ContractReturnValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.codeInspection.dataFlow.ContractReturnValue
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ContractReturnValue.BooleanReturnValue, ContractReturnValue.ParameterReturnValue

    public abstract class ContractReturnValue
extends java.lang.Object
    Representation of MethodContract return value. It may represent the concrete value (e.g. "false") or pose some constraints to the method return value (e.g. "!null").

      • getMethodCompatibilityProblem

        public final java.lang.String getMethodCompatibilityProblem(PsiMethod method)
        Checks whether this return value makes sense for the specified method signature. The method body is not checked. E.g. "true" contract value makes sense for method returning boolean, but does not make sense for method returning int. This method can be used to check the contract correctness.
        Parameters:
        method -
        Returns:
        null if this contract return value makes sense for the supplied return type. Otherwise the human-readable error message is returned.

      • isMethodCompatible

        public final boolean isMethodCompatible(PsiMethod method)
        Checks whether this return value makes sense for the specified method signature. The method body is not checked. E.g. "true" contract value makes sense for method returning boolean, but does not make sense for method returning int. This method can be used to check the contract correctness.
        Parameters:
        method -
        Returns:
        true if this contract return value makes sense for the supplied return type.

      • isValueCompatible

        public abstract boolean isValueCompatible(DfaMemoryState state,
                                          DfaValue value)
        Returns true if the supplied DfaValue could be compatible with this return value. If false is returned, then returning given DfaValue would violate the contract with this return value. This method can be used to check the contract correctness.
        Parameters:
        state - memory state to use
        value - value to check
        Returns:
        whether the supplied value could be compatible with this return value.

      • ordinal

        public int ordinal()
        Returns a unique non-negative number which identifies this return value. Can be used for serialization. For two return values a and b the following holds: a.ordinal() == b.ordinal() <=> a.equals(b).
        Returns:
        a unique non-negative number which identifies this return value.

      • valueOf

        public static ContractReturnValue valueOf(int ordinal)
        Returns a ContractReturnValue which corresponds to given ordinal index. For any return value x the following holds: ContractReturnValue.valueOf(x.ordinal()).equals(x).
        Parameters:
        ordinal - ordinal to create a ContractReturnValue object from
        Returns:
        a ContractReturnValue object. Returns an object which represents any possible value if the supplied ordinal does not correspond to any valid ContractReturnValue.

      • valueOf

        public static ContractReturnValue valueOf(java.lang.String value)
        Returns a ContractReturnValue which corresponds to given string representation. For any return value x the following holds: ContractReturnValue.valueOf(x.toString()).equals(x) and for string str the following holds: ContractReturnValue.valueOf(str) == null || ContractReturnValue.valueOf(str).toString().equals(str).
        Parameters:
        value - string representation of return value
        Returns:
        ContractReturnValue object which corresponds to given string representation; null if given value is not supported.
